x4freetext: pulse width is aprx. 1 ns, repetition rate 250 KHz,
Protons have energy 1912 keV, 31 keV above 7Li(p,n)
reaction threshold which yields continuous neutron
energy distribution with high energy cutoff at 106
keV. Resulting neutrons are emitted into a forward
cone with 120 degrees opening angle. The angle-integ-
rated spectrum peaks at 25 keV. This gives approx.
Maxwellian spectrum with temperature kT=25+-0.5 keV
The investigated Sm, Eu, and Er samples were sandwiched
between 0.03 mm thick gold foils of the same diameter
for normalization to the well-known (n,gamma) cross
section of 197-Au (648+-10 mb at kT=25 keV)
